The paper focuses on the use of neuroevolution techniques to optimize neural network architectures, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and frameworks such as Keras, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments performed in the paper involve image classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed technique in control systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
